==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prosaical
<hw>Pro*sa"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>prosaius</ets>, from
<ets>prosa</ets> prose: cf. F,. <ets>prosa⟦ium⟧que</ets>. See
<er>Prose</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to prose;
resembling prose; in the form of prose; unpoetical; writing or using
prose; <as>as, a <ex>prosaic</ex> composition</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dull; uninteresting; commonplace; unimaginative;
prosy; <as>as, a <ex>prosaic</ex> person</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ed.
Rev.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pro*sa"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pro*sa"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prosaicism</ent>⟦br⟧
